Parliament, Tuesday 30 March 2021 – National Assembly Speaker Ms Thandi Modise will deliver a Human Rights public lecture themed: “Promoting Human Rights in the Age of Covid-19” at the National Heritage Council of South Africa (NHC) tomorrow.
	
	The lecture, organised by the NHC, is a celebration of Nelson Mandela’s generational legacy of Human Rights in the year of Charlotte Maxeke. The Speaker is expected to draw on her extensive personal experience in the liberation struggle and the building of a new society to reflect on the concepts of Human Rights, Liberation Struggle and Reconciliation as part of Nelson Mandela’s generational legacy.
	
	Details of the public lecture are as follows:
	
	Date: Wednesday, 31 March 2021
	Time: 11h00
	Venue: Virtual platforms
	
	Members of the media who would like to be part of the Public Lecture may forward their contact details to Mr Mlindi Mpindi on mmpindi@parliament.gov.za for inclusion in the Parliamentary Communication Services WhatsApp group, where login details will be shared. Journalists must forward these requests using their official email addresses (no private emails).
	
	Members of the public may follow the virtual engagement live through a live stream on Parliament’s YouTube channel and Twitter page on the links below. You may subscribe to the Parliament YouTube channel to receive instant notification of live feeds. The lecture will be scheduled for later broadcast on Parliament TV (DSTV Channel 408).
	
	Twitter: https://twitter.com/ParliamentofRSA
	Facebook: https://facebook.com/ParliamentofRSA
	YouTube: https://www.youtube.com/ParliamentofRSA
	
